Appendix B: Parameter Table with Baseline Values & Sources

This table provides empirically grounded starting points for simulation. All values are illustrative and must be calibrated for specific regional or global analyses.

Parameter Symbol Baseline Value (Range) Unit Justification & Source
Economic Parameters    
Research Productivity  \eta  0.01 - 0.05 Dimensionless Calibrated to match historical TFP growth (Jones, 1995).
Returns to Research Scale  \lambda  0.6 - 0.8 Dimensionless Consistent with diminishing returns to R&D effort (Bloom et al., 2020).
Knowledge Spillover  \phi  0.4 - 0.6 Dimensionless Ensures "standing on shoulders" effect without explosive growth.
Capital Elasticity  \alpha  0.33 Dimensionless Standard value from macroeconomics.
SGI Capability Parameters    
Raw SGI Efficiency Growth  g_{\sigma_{\text{raw}}}  10% - 50% p.a. Annual % Based on extrapolations of frontier AI training compute trends (OpenAI, 2023).
Initial SGI Stock  \text{SGI}(t_0)  1 (normalized) Dimensionless Normalization point for relative scaling.
Physical System Parameters    
Compute Energy Density  \rho_{\text{power}}  1,000 - 20,000 W/m² Critical. Air-cooled DC: ~1k W/m². Advanced liquid: >20k W/m². Stagnation is key risk.
Clean Energy Growth Rate  g_{S_{\text{clean}}}  3% - 7% p.a. Annual % IEA NZE Scenario vs. Stated Policies Scenario (IEA, 2023).
Mineral Supply Inelasticity Elasticity of  S_i  0.1 - 0.3 Dimensionless Short-term supply is highly inelastic (World Bank, 2020).
Cooling Tech Coefficient  \eta_T  0.05 - 0.15 Dimensionless Efficiency of SGI at improving cooling tech (e.g., optofluidic, radiative).
Governance & Policy Parameters    
SGI Allocation to Energy  f_{\text{alloc}, E}  0.1 - 0.5 Fraction Primary policy lever for "Green Discontinuity."
SGI Allocation to Materials  f_{\text{alloc}, M}  0.05 - 0.2 Fraction 
SGI Allocation to Cooling  f_{\text{alloc}, T}  0.05 - 0.3 Fraction Critical for overcoming  \rho_{\text{power}}  bottleneck.
Convertibility: Energy  \eta_E  0.1 - 0.4 Dimensionless SGI's assumed efficacy in fusion, grid, storage R&D.
Labor Displacement Rate  \beta  0.02 - 0.1 p.a. Annual % Based on task exposure estimates (Eloundou et al., 2023).
Base New Task Creation  \gamma_0  0.01 - 0.03 p.a. Annual % Historical background rate of occupational innovation.

